Interpretation Notes

  • Experience vs Edge: Cross-platform React Native and web clients connect through CDN/WAF and the API gateway, which handles rate limiting, JWT validation, and OIDC handshakes prior to the mesh.
  • Channel BFFs: Separate BFF deployments protect downstream services from tight coupling; graph edges show how each BFF composes domain APIs.
  • Domain Services: .NET 8 services follow Clean Architecture with dependency injection, exposing REST/FHIR endpoints secured by the mesh.
  • Integration Layer: Red Hat Fuse, DICOM adapters, and AMQ Streams reside within the mesh, guaranteeing encrypted transport back to provincial systems.
  • Data Stores: Redis is explicitly non-PHI; PostgreSQL only retains tokenized consent/preferences; Audit object storage provides WORM retention for compliance.
  • Platform Services: Vault, OPA, OTel, and Jenkins-led CI with Wiz/SonarQube/Black Duck feed FluxCD GitOps delivery; all interactions occur over mTLS enforced by the mesh, with the enterprise registry storing signed images.
